parameters.name: ACLT_EGRclr_Lmin
parameters.definition: Estimated auxiliary coolant flow through the EGR cooler (equal to the intercooler bypass flow).

parameters.name: ACLT_EGRclr_min_Lmin
parameters.definition: Minimum heat exchanger flow rate required to avoid thermal shock / damage to the heat exchangers.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_dT_halt
parameters.definition: If the actual temperature is within +/- this amount of the target temperature, the valve command is frozen until the temperature error exceeds the 'resume' deadzone below.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_dT_res
parameters.definition: If control updates are halted and the difference between the actual and target temperatures exceed this amount (+ or -), control updates will resume.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_ena
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split output channel.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_I_accum
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split integral accumulator.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_Ki
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split CL Ki gain.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_Kp
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split CL Kp gain.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_Lmin_CL
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split total closed-loop correction.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_T_cmd
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split temperature target. This is calculated as the maximum of the auxiliary coolant temperature and the post-intercooler dew point, plus the temperature target offset.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_T_error
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split temperature error.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_T_ofs

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_act

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_cmd
parameters.definition: Auxiliary coolant control intercooler/EGR cooler flow split valve command.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_def
parameters.definition: This position is commanded to the intercooler/EGR valve prior to engine shutdown to guarantee operation following a cold shutdown. 0% = no intercooler bypass; 100% = full radiator bypass.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_halt
parameters.definition: Indicates the intercooler/EGR valve control is halted due to a temperature error within the calibrated deadzone.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_max
parameters.definition: Maximum intercooler bypass valve position.

parameters.name: ACLT_intby_vlv_min
parameters.definition: Minimum intercooler bypass valve position.

parameters.name: ACLT_intclr_dTh_ff

parameters.name: ACLT_intTlim_T_max
